args: Gotcha! Now let's get you back to—
One day, everything that brings you\nhappiness will be gone.
And the more happiness you feel,\nthe greater the sadness will be\nwhen that time comes.
That's why you shouldn't go back\nto the village.
You're going to have to live for a very\nlong time—longer than your friends in\nthe village, and longer than your parents.
And once you have to say goodbye\nto all of that, all that will be left\ninside of you will be...rain.
It will rain forever in your heart;\nan eternal downpour of loneliness.
Yes. But it doesn't have to be like that;\nI can take you to a sylvan village so you\ncan be with your own kind.
If you leave your parents now,\nyou won't have to face the pain\nof saying goodbye later.
I promised Mama and Papa that\nwe'd go into town together soon,\nand it's bad to break your promises.
I wanna do that AND a bunch of other\nfun stuff with them, so I'm going home!
But I need MORE good memories to\nstuff in the vault, which is why I'm\nalways tryin' to search out fun stuff.
(More memories for the vault\nin your heart...)
Fine. If that's what you want,\nI'll take you back home.
...It's too quiet here. Where is everyone?\nWhere's Nadine?
Weeeell? I did pretty good, huh?
Better to have perished in battle than be\ncaptured by this foolish slip of a girl!
You caught the commander!\nDoes that mean...?
Heck yeah! Our united front saved the day!
Were you scared? Did they hurt you?
No. The nice lady saved me.
It's you...\nThank you so much, miss.
I just brought her back like she wanted.
My wife and I have been thinking\nabout what you told us.

It's exactly as you say: No matter how
much care we put into raising her,
we will be gone from this world while
she is still beginning her time in it.
That's right. She'll be alone\nfor a long, long time.
Even when we are gone, she will still\nmeet new people that support her—\nand that she will support in turn.
That's why we want to leave her with\nproof that she was loved—so she can\ncarry those memories with her forever.
So long as she has those in her heart,\nI'm certain she will be happy.
(Did they try to leave me with\na lifetime of happy memories?)
*gasp* Girl, you remembered my name!\nOmigosh, I can't EVEN with you!\nAre we BFFs now?!
How could I forget it when you\nnever stop talking to me?\nNow, what did you want?
Oh, right! So I wanna commemorate\nour glorious victory before prince dude\nand all those other folks get back.
Let's snap a few pics so we'll never forget\nall the great memories we made!

Duh! Of COURSE I'll remember you!
...Hey, wait. Are you, like, camera shy?
Have I actually been super annoying
you this entire time?
I...want to be in a picture with you.
Seriously? You're not just doing this\nto shut me up or whatever?
No. When I saw your pictures,\nI knew I wanted to be in one.
No lonely rain will ever fall\nin your pretty pictures.
Holy crap, that is, like, a poem...\nOkay, then cram in here so we can\nmake a new memory, girl!
Oh, wait! We need a good background!\nLet's go get the boat and bring it around.
That seems like a lot of work.
There are no compromises when it\ncomes to making good memories!
Well, I suppose it should look nice...
See, I knew you'd get it.\nNow let's get going!
'Cause our next mission together is\nto find the best shot of us EVER!
